snippet: Toll Brothers said its earnings dropped to $46.6 million, or 26 cents a share, in the quarter ended July 31, compared with $61.6 million, or 36 cents a share, a year ago.
abstract: Toll Brothers reports fiscal third-quarter profit of $46.6 million, or 26 cents a share, down 24 percent compared with $61.6 million, or 36 cents a share, in year-ago quarter; revenue rose 24 percent to $689.2 million.
lead_paragraph: Toll Brothers said its earnings dropped to $46.6 million, or 26 cents a share, in the quarter ended July 31, compared with $61.6 million, or 36 cents a share, a year ago.

headline.main: Toll Brothers Profit Falls, but the Builder’s Optimism Rises
